d and the PM signal keeps leaning hard one way at fair-value prices. That is exactly the kind of setup that tempts entries while the fast tape is still too unstable.\n\n**Decision:** Keep P4 posture **defensive / watchlist-only**. Do **not** add any PM confidence boost from the funding squeeze and do **not** loosen weekend or fast-regime gates. Treat `mixed_transition + high PM risk + strong one-sided bias near 0.50` as a candidate for a future smart-entry penalty test.\n\n**Next:** On the next Pillar 4 pass, watch for fast-regime cooldown. If classifier moves `mixed_transition -> range_compression_setup` or `range_mean_revert_friendly` while PM stays near 0.50, that becomes a viable weekday watchlist. If fast regime stays **HIGH_VOL**, keep filtering.\n\n## 2026-05-02 22:20 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL live trader now publishes direct state instead of hiding behind log inference\n\n**Task:** Convert HL directional monitoring from log-only inference into a direct state surface owned by the active live process, then verify the dashboard can d",
